The memorandum is a delegation of authority from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development. The authority being delegated is the power to designate an employee of a relevant federal department or agency to serve on the Coalition for Epidemic Preparedness Innovations (CEPI) Investors Council and, if nominated, on the CEPI Board of Directors as a representative of the United States. This delegation of authority is in accordance with section 6501(b)(2) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2022. The memorandum also states that this delegation applies to any future public law that contains the same or substantially the same provision. The Administrator is directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.